xpertise in the purchase of materials which effectively support current programs and enhance scholarly content in disciplines  Materials acquired through this program are integrated into Preston Library s collections  Departmental allocations are determined early in the annual budget process  Once Preston Library s final fiscal year budget is known  the monograph budget is determined  Approximately one half of the monograph budget is used by library staff for overall collection development  The remaining half is allocated to academic departments for collection development  Library staff review and determine allocations for individual departments and majors based on current academic year priorities  Allocation program funds are based on VMI s fiscal year  unused funds are not carried over to the next fiscal year  Reference librarians  COL Janet Holly and MAJ Accacia Mullen  routinely work with faculty to identify relevant materials for a wide array of programs  In addition  Acquisitions staff in Preston Library  Ms  Susan LeMert  sends Choice Reviews on Cards  Choice cards  to each academic department s Library Liaison to assist in the selection process  Departments are not limited to Choice purchases and may suggest purchases throughout the academic year  Questions regarding allocation balances should be directed to Ms  Susan LeMert  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 